Japanese: ジャンジャック＿操縦やられ
アンマリー＿ちょっとした驚き

なんで……。
ジャックが負けるなんて……
ケイ＿イライラして喋るＬ

まだそんなこといってんのか。
信じられないバカだぜ。
English: Are you still saying stuff like that? I can't believe how stupid you are.

Japanese: ケイ＿イライラして喋るＬ

ナイトシェイドとの戦いを
思い出せよ。
English: Remember what happened in the battle against Nightshade.

Japanese:
今、
マリオネーションギアの技術は、
すごい勢いで進歩してる。
English: The art of Marionation Gear has been progressing at an incredible pace nowadays.

Japanese:
ダンクールに何百年の歴史が
あるか知らねぇけどさ。
English: I don't know anything about the Dancourt's supposed hundreds of years of history.

Japanese:
今、この瞬間、
本当に強いのは……
ダンクールなんかじゃない。
English: But, at this moment, the true strength.. isn't in the Dancourt name.

Japanese:
人形技術の最先端をになう者。
/pやアンマリーだ。
English: It's with those who are leading the forefront of mech technology, /p and Anne-Marie.

Japanese: みんながそう言ってたろ。

それに、
オレが整備した人形だぜ。
English: Besides, those are mechs which have been maintained by the one and only, me.

Japanese: ジャンジャック＿操縦くやしい

English: The Dancourt name has been defeated...

Japanese:
何やってんだ。
こんなところで。

まあ、いろいろ考えることが
あるわけですか……。
English: Well, I guess you must have a few things to rethink now, huh...?

Japanese:
お前の弟、
だいぶショック受けてたな。
English: Your little brother probably got quite the shock.

Japanese:
ジャックは、負けたこと
ないから……。

……私、ずっと
落ちこぼれだった……。
English: ...I've been lagging behind this whole time...

Japanese:
何をやってもダメだったし……
ずっと弟と比べられて……
English: Nothing I did was ever good enough... Not when compared to my brother...

Japanese:
なんでも
あいつの方がうまくできた……。
English: No matter what it was, he was always better than me...
I was trying to escape by coming here...
I wanted to get away from my brother...

Japanese:
無理言って
修行に出してもらった。
English: I said I was going to do some difficult training.

Japanese:
遠くの街の
小さな工房を選んで……。
English: So I chose a small workshop in a city far, far away...

Japanese:
……いいんじゃねぇか。
そんなことは。
お前だって、強くなったよ。
English: Because of that, you've gotten stronger.

Japanese:
今じゃ、/pと、
そんなに差はないだろ。
English: Right now, there's not that much difference between you and /p.

Japanese:
弟より、
お前の方が強いんだぜ。
English: Compared to your brother, you're much stronger.

Japanese:
……そんなこと
考えたこともなかった。
English: ...I've never thought of it like that.

Japanese:
ここへ来てから、いろいろ
がんばってきただろ。
English: Since arriving here, you've been trying your best at various things.
...Why are you being so nice to me?

Japanese:
ガロイ工房の３バカだろ。
俺たちは。
English: The three weirdos at the Galouye Workshop. That's us.

Japanese: 私、あんたたちのこと、好きよ。
